Dominance and trustworthiness

Organize data for graphing dominance and trustworthiness differences

data_mean_dt <- data %>%
  group_by(trait) %>%
  summarize_at(vars(BM_BW:AM_AW), mean)

data_sd_dt <- data %>%
  group_by(trait) %>%
  summarize_at(vars(BM_BW:AM_AW), sd)

data_graph_dt_wide <- data.frame(t(rbind(data_mean_dt, data_sd_dt)))[c(2:7),]
names(data_graph_dt_wide) <- c("mean_d", "mean_t", "SD_d", "SD_t")

data_graph_d <- data_graph_dt_wide[,c(1,3)]
names(data_graph_d) <- c("mean", "SD")
data_graph_d$trait <- "Dominant"
data_graph_t <- data_graph_dt_wide[,c(2,4)]
names(data_graph_t) <- c("mean", "SD")
data_graph_t$trait <- "Trustworthy"

data_graph_dt <- rbind(data_graph_d, data_graph_t)
data_graph_dt$mean <- as.numeric(data_graph_dt$mean)
data_graph_dt$SD <- as.numeric(data_graph_dt$SD)

data_graph_dt$SE <- data_graph_dt$SD/sqrt((nrow(data)/2))
data_graph_dt$LCI <- data_graph_dt$mean - 1.96*data_graph_dt$SE
data_graph_dt$UCI <- data_graph_dt$mean + 1.96*data_graph_dt$SE

data_graph_dt$RaceGender <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

data_graph_dt$RaceGender <- fct_inorder(data_graph_dt$RaceGender)

data_graph_labels <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

Graph summary of dominance trustworthiness comparison

sim_graph_dt <- ggplot(data_graph_dt, aes(group = trait, x = RaceGender, y = mean, ymin = LCI, ymax = UCI, color = trait)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  geom_point(size=2.5, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=15),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels=data_graph_labels) +
  ylab("Mean Similarity Score") +
  #scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(3.5, 4, 4.5, 5, 5.5), limits=c(3.4, 5.8)) +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("#339966", "#FFCC66"))

Creating tidy summaries of t-tests by dominance and trustworthiness

ttest_graph_dt <- rbind(tidy(Test7), tidy(Test8), tidy(Test9), tidy(Test10), tidy(Test11), tidy(Test12))

ttest_graph_dt$Comparison <- c("Black Man\nBlack Woman", "Black Man\nAsian Man", "Black Man\nAsian Woman",
                          "Black Woman\nAsian Man", "Black Woman\nAsian Woman", "Asian Man\nAsian Woman")

ttest_graph_dt$Comparison <- fct_inorder(ttest_graph_dt$Comparison)

Create graph of difference scores for dominance and trustworthiness with 95% CIs

diff_graph_dt <- ggplot(ttest_graph_dt, aes(x = Comparison, y = estimate, ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, color="#2e5a5c") +
  geom_point(size=2.5, color="#2e5a5c") +
  geom_hline(yintercept=0) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  ylab("Difference (Dom - Trust)")

Combine with patchwork

combined_graph_dt <- sim_graph_dt + diff_graph_dt + plot_layout(ncol=1) + plot_annotation(title = "<span style='color:#339966;'>Dominance</span> and <span style='color:#FFCC66;'>Trustworthiness</span> Similarity Scores Without Occupation (and Their <span style='color:#2e5a5c;'>Difference</span>)", theme = theme(plot.title = element_markdown(lineheight = 1.1, size = 17, hjust=.5)))

ggsave("figures/combined_p2_dt.jpg", height=8, width=10, unit="in", dpi=600)
knitr::include_graphics("figures/combined_p2_dt.jpg")

Interaction between occupation and trait

Restructuring the data

data$id <- row.names(data)

data_l <- pivot_longer(data=data, cols=c(BM_BW:AMO_AWO), names_to = "targets", values_to = "similarity")

data_l$Occupation <- ifelse(str_detect(data_l$targets, "O") == TRUE, 1, 0)

data_l$Comparison <- str_remove_all(data_l$targets, "O")

data_l$trait <- as.factor(data_l$trait)
data_l$trait_rev <- fct_rev(data_l$trait)

Fitting multilevel models and examining cross-level interactions and simple slopes

dt_int <- lmer(similarity ~ trait*Occupation + (Occupation|id), data=data_l)

#summ(BM_BW_int_wrong)
summ(dt_int, confint=TRUE, digits=3)
